  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 67\u0d9a \u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca \u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dbb\u0dd0\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "67 lakh gold cannot be taken to America",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A group of customs officers arrested a Sri Lankan American national who tried to illegally take three gold biscuits worth 67 lakhs and 50 thousand rupees to the United States without declaring them to the customs.",
        "He is a 42-year-old Sri Lankan resident of the United States of America. He arrived at Katunayake airport at 10.05 am to board the Emirates flight EK-651 departing for Dubai.",
        "He went to Dubai and from there he arrived at the Katunayake airport preparing to leave for the United States of America. The three gold biscuits weighing 300 grams, which were carefully hidden in the suitcase he brought, were found by the customs officials and arrested."
      ],
